snippet.textDisplay:
While Abdul Hannan's voice has a touch of modern flavor to it, it still blends with the music beautifully. And then, Jaffer Zaidi comes in to steal your heart with the very first 'alaap' in his magical and vintage vocals.
The music has a genuine 'Kaavish' stamp all through the song. So well composed and beautifully written.
'Andar teray raaz kayi hein'. Man what lyricism.
Another masterpiece. Keep them coming, Coke Studio.
PS: the hymn towards the end ❤👌
